      "text": "Try to Download directly (1.70 MB) Play Press play then disable your screen reader. Use space bar to pause or play, and up and down arrows to control volume. Use left arrow to rewind and right arrow to fast forward. Image: Consumer group wants service time guarantees for telcos \nBy George Roberts on The World Today Share Download (1.70 MB) MP3 available 1.70 MB \nA group representing consumers wants new regulations to force the internet companies and the National Broadband Network to fix service problems within a guaranteed timeframe. \nThe latest figures from the telecommunications ombudsman show there was a blow-out in NBN related complaints by 160 per cent last financial year. \nThe Australian Communications Consumer Action Network, wants the telecommunications consumer protections code reviewed. Duration: 3min 42sec Broadcast: Wed 18 Oct 2017, 12:51pm More Information \nAndrea Dowsett, student and NBN customerStephen Jones, Federal Opposition Regional Communications spokesmanNarelle Clark, deputy CEO, Australian Communications Consumer Action Network Credits",
