      "text": "Arrest made as police clash with children on scooters 22nd Oct 2017 5:50 PM Police have clashed with children over scooters Trevor Veale Use this content by Jack McKay \nPOLICE have arrested a youth following a scuffle with a large group of young people who were allegedly riding dangerously on scooters through Brisbane's CBD. \nFootage showed several police officers involved in a scuffle with some of the young scooter riders. \nPolice allege the group were travelling the wrong way down roads and were \"weaving in out of traffic\". \n\"It appears as though the ride was organised via social media,\" police said in a statement. \n\"Preliminary information suggests that police were not advised of this so-called event prior to it happening. \n\"Police have been liaising with parents who have been arriving at Kangaroo Point to collect their children.\" \nPolice believe the group was heading towards Kangaroo Point. \nInvestigations into the incident are ongoing. No charges have been laid. Related Items",
