      "host": "howimetlaundrylan.com.au",
      "text": "by Jose Rojas Spanish in Greece \nBy the end of August of 2015, I had already travelled solo for almost 1 month around Europe. \nAt that time, I was in Greece, where I was going to spend about 1 week in total. I started with Athens and then took a ferry to Santorini. \nOn my first day, I was looking for the port of Fira but I got lost, so I kept walking. I was so awed with the scenery that I kept walking for over 3 hours until I got to the town of Oia. Have you ever seen any of those postcards with those white houses and blue rounded roofs? That is the place! \nAnyway, on my second day I managed to find the port of Fira and I took a cable car to get down there. \nOnce I was there, I took this group tour on a boat to visit some hotsprings and a volcano. \nWhen we were reaching the hotsprings, the boat just stopped in the middle of nowhere and they told us that we had to jump and swim on deep water to get to the hotsprings. \nThen I appreciated that my mum signed me up to swimming classes when I was a kid. \nSo I took my t-shirt off, jumped off the boat and swam like there was no tomorrow. And when I arrived to the hotsprings something unexpected happened: I was hearing someone speaking Spanish right behind me. \nSo I introduced myself. \nThey were 3 girls living in Barcelona who took a week off work to travel together around Greece. \nAnd they seemed pretty astonished when I told them that I had been travelling solo for a month and that I was moving to Melbourne after that trip. \nWe stuck together for a while and rode some donkeys uphill to go back to Fira. I was at the front during that ride, and at some point this girl took her camera off and made me a photo from the distance. \nCoincidentally, we were going to go to Crete next on the same day and almost at the same time, so we met again before catching the ferry and then we met again in Crete. \nThey rented a car to drive around that island and I joined them for a day. We went to this beach of which name I can’t remember, but I do remember it was far away from town and that it was incredibly beautiful. \nI got to know them a bit more personally and they told me a few of their stories. One of them said to me that she got a restraining order against her ex. Other mentioned that she was really from Galicia but moved to Barcelona a few years ago for work. \nAfter the beach, I went back to town and they continued their drive. I exchanged phone numbers with the girl who took that photo of me riding the donkey. Then we parted ways and never saw each other again. \n…or that’s what I thought that would happen. I will tell you what really happened with them on my next posts! Share this:",
