      "url": "http://www.smh.com.au/world/new-zealands-first-cat-takes-to-twitter-as-mum-jacinda-ardern-finalises-cabinet-20171024-gz732s.html",
      "host": "smh.com.au",
      "text": "An official announcement: 'Hi, I'm Paddles and I am the First Cat of New Zealand'. Photo: Twitter/@FirstCatofNZ \nThere is speculation that Ardern's partner, fishing TV show host Clarke Gayford, is behind the social media presence. So far, there's been no official confirmation as to who is running the account that has published scores of tweets and amassed thousands of followers. \nThe feline's Twitter bio describes her as an \"Independent cat - not affurliated with the Labour Pawty\". Related Articles Sudden star Jacinda Ardern promises 'fairer deal' for NZ \nShe's also not terribly interested in politics, in response to a follower's tweet, the First Cat said: \"All I care about is a good box tbh. Mum will deal with those politicat pawlicies\". \nWhile her \"mother\" is taking calls from the likes of Justin Trudeau and Donald Trump , Paddles has been greeted online by the US Ambassador to New Zealand's 'Diplo Dog' Gracie Brown. Advertisement \nPaddles has also already quipped with former prime minister John Key's cat Moonbeam for having \"no grip on social media\" and \"no opposable thumbs\" and made countless jokes about her favourite food - fish - plus a range of social issues. You will now receive updates from Breaking News Alert Breaking News Alert \nGet the latest news and updates emailed straight to your inbox. By submitting your email you are agreeing to Fairfax Media's terms and conditions and privacy policy . \nMeanwhile Ardern and her soon-to-be deputy, Winston Peters, signed the official agreement tying their two parties together on Tuesday. SHARE Share on Twitter TWEET Link New Zealand Prime Minister-designate Jacinda Ardern takes a Skype call from Canadian PM Justin Trudeau in Wellington on Tuesday. Photo: Handout/AP \nA second ceremony was to be held later in the afternoon to confirm Labour's confidence and supply agreement with the Green Party. \nThe agreement outlines portfolio positions for NZ First - four ministerial postings inside cabinet and a parliamentary undersecretary. SHARE",
