      "text": "Viking Cruises has announced a further two new cruise extensions to its Alaska & the Inside Passage ocean itinerary – the 8-day Canadian Rockies and the 7-day Pristine Alaska. \n“We recently launched our shorter 3-day Anchorage extension and the 6-day Denali Explorer with Anchorage & Talkeetna extension, and we have been overwhelmed by their popularity,” said Lubica Sibikova, Product Manager Viking Cruises Australia and New Zealand. \n“The launch of the longer extensions to Alaska & the Inside Passage ocean itinerary is in response to the wishes of our travel-curious guests, who can now discover even more of what these stunning destinations have to offer and enjoy an in-depth Alaska and Canada experience.” \nThe Canadian Rockies lets guests discover Banff National Park, Jasper, Johnston Canyon and Vancouver, while Pristine Alaska includes stops in Anchorage, Talkeetna, Denali National Park, and Fairbanks. \nThe 11-day Alaska & the Inside Passage cruise from Vancouver to Seward or vice versa, sails between May and August 2019 from $6,695 per person. This ocean cruise features seven guided tours in Canada and the United States’ Alaska. Book before 31 December 2017 and save $1,000 per couple. \nAdd the 8-day cruise extension Canadian Rockies from $5,339pp, or the 7-day cruise extension Pristine Alaska from $4,939pp. More extensions for Viking’s Alaska ocean cruise itinerary was last modified: October 24th, 2017 by TM staff writer",
