      "text": "Try to Download directly (1.60 MB) Play Press play then disable your screen reader. Use space bar to pause or play, and up and down arrows to control volume. Use left arrow to rewind and right arrow to fast forward. Image: High court rules against Tasmanian anti protest laws \nBy Felicity Ogilvie on The World Today Share Download (1.60 MB) MP3 available 1.60 MB \nThe former Australian Greens Leader Bob Brown has won a High Court case against the Tasmanian Government's anti protest laws. \nThe laws were designed to stop protests in the forests and Bob Brown was arrested while protesting against logging last year. \nThe High Court found the laws \"are invalid because they impermissibly burden the implied freedom of political communication contrary to the Commonwealth Constitution.\" Duration: 3min 29sec Broadcast: Wed 18 Oct 2017, 12:12pm More Information \nBob Brown , former Greens Leader, environmental activist Credits",
