      "host": "sconeadvocate.com.au",
      "text": "twitter TWEET \nTHE final figure is in for the Murrurundi Bowling Club’s annual fundraising event held on September 30. \nA few dollars short of $7,500 was rasied – with all money to be generously donated to Scone Cancer Support Group. \nMembers of the community donned pink or blue for the ‘Boys Night In With The Girls’ barefoot bowls day, aimed at raising funds for both prostate and breast cancer. \nMurrurundi Bowling Club manager Leanne Mills said it was a fantastic day thanks to the support of local businesses. \n“Jeff Stephen has been our major supporter for the past four years and we are very grateful for his help,” she said. \n“Along with the rest of the local businesses that supported our day including the Railway Hotel, Whitehart Hotel, Just Deb's, Adawn, Scone Timber & Hardware, Icebox Liquor Scone, 8 Ball Aitken, Murrurundi Public School P&C and Chubber's Lawn Mowing. \n“And, of course Peter Sawyer our auctioneer who extracted as much cash as possible from guests. \n“We would also like to thank one of our staff members Tania Geary – this has been her baby right from the start and she works tirelessly to make the day a success,” Ms Mills said. \nThe final figure of $7,487 will be donated to Scone and District Cancer Support Group, helping to make the lives of those suffering from cancer easier by providing much needed equipment. \n“We chose the Scone Cancer Support Group because we believe that it is very important that all funds are used locally to help our community,” Ms Mills said. \n“Once again thank you to all that helped to make a day a great success.”",
