      "text": "twitter TWEET Quality: The spirited bidding throughout the sale reflected the calibre of the rams on offer. Photo: Supplied. \nA good even line-up of rams greeted clients at the annual Bark Hut white suffolk and composite ram sale at Andrew and Bec Bennett’s Stony Creek Property, at Rowland Hill Highway, KI, on Thursday, October 5. \nOn offer were 70 composite and 37 white suffolk rams which attracted a larger crowd than last year and included new and repeat buyers. \nElders Stud stock auctioneer Tony Weatherall sang the praises of the livestock on offer. \nHe complimented the owners on the presentation of the stock in a year that had been pretty tough. \nThe sale commenced with composite rams which reached a top price of $2400 to GA & JA Buick and NRG Campbell, whose ram presented an eye muscle width of 85 depth of 42 and index of 1090. \nMultiple buyers include WA Buttrose, JA & AC Ness and Dunn Pastoral P/L, and others that pushed the average price of the composites to $1230 with a 100 per cent clearance of stock. \nThe white suffolks followed up again, impressing with a top price of $1600 sold to JM Boyle & DJ Willmott for a ram with eye muscle width 87 depth 41 and index of 1126. \nMultiple buyers included MG Florance and MJ & RJ Vogt with other bidders pushing the average price to over $970. \nThe 2017 overall average price pushed up from 2016 from $882.00 to $1,147. \nOwners Andrew and Bec Bennett said they were very pleased with the sale result. \nThe Bennett family would also like to thank their clients for the ongoing support and wish them success with their purchases.",
