      "host": "northernstar.com.au",
      "text": "Husband of slain teacher arrested 24th Oct 2017 6:45 PM Use this content by Staff Writer \nKENYAN police have arrested the husband of Australian teacher Gabrielle Maina and another man in connection with her murder. \nMs Maina, a mother of two originally from Armidale in NSW, was shot dead on a street in Nairobi last Thursday. \nHer estranged husband, Cyrus Bernard Maina Njuguna, and another man, John Njuguna Waithira have been arrested in connection with her death, the ABC is reporting. \nNo charges have been laid yet. Gabrielle Maina was shot and killed in Nairobi. \nA post-mortem found Ms Maina died from a single gunshot wound to the neck. \nMs Maina moved to Kenya in 2015, and was the head teacher at Hillcrest Preparatory School in Karen. She had previously worked as a teacher in NSW and attended university at the University of New England in Armidale.",
