      "text": "What Recent Ownership Trends Suggest About Applied Materials, Inc. (AMAT)’s Future Performance By - October 24, 2017 \nRecent trading patterns in the stock of Applied Materials, Inc. (NASDAQ:AMAT) have investors on high alert. Many experts agree that the best way to predict future performance is by studying the past. In the cast of AMAT, these trading patterns could have some important implications for future performance. In the most recent quarter, institutional ownership increased by a net of 4.81 million shares, or 0.55%. This is a bullish sign and indicates that institutions are feeling more optimistic about the outlook for AMAT overall. 398 holders increased their positions, 470 decreased their positions, and 139 holders held their positions. \nAmong institutions that increased their positions, 110 were new positions. Among holders that decreased their positions, 60 sold out of the stock Applied Materials, Inc.. Insider ownership during the latest quarter increased by a net of 51677 shares, indicating that AMAT’s key executives are feeling more bullish about the stock than they did three months ago. 1 or 20% of the trades during the past quarter were buys, and 4 or 80% were sells. This activity represents a continuation of a theme over the past twelve months. Insider ownership during the last year has increased by a net of 637203 shares. 43.18% of insider trades in the last 12 months were buys, and 56.82% were sells. \nOver the past year, the price of Applied Materials, Inc. (AMAT) has increased 98.28% while the S&P 500 has increased 19.69%. During the past 20 days, AMAT has increased 21.67% while the broad market has increased 2.88%. AMAT ‘s 20-day moving average currently sits below its 100-day moving average. This is a bearish signal that suggests the stock price might have farther to fall. AMAT’s average trading volume during the past 20 days is lower than the average volume over the past 100 days, which could be an indication that investors are feeling less certain than usual about the direction of AMAT’s future price movements. \nApplied Materials, Inc. (NASDAQ:AMAT) has a 20-day RSI of 76.62%. According to this momentum indicator, a reading above 70 suggests the stock is entering overbought territory and that the recent uptrend may be about to reverse. The MACD tells a similair story. AMAT’s 9-day MACD currently sits below the 20-day MACD, indicating that AMAT’s upside momentum has decreased during the last three weeks. This suggests that the trend might soon reverse. AMAT’s average trading volatility during the past few weeks is -10.29% lower than the average volatility over the past 100 days. This means that the stock’s daily price swings have been less extreme in recent times compared to the past. \nAnalysts expect Applied Materials, Inc. (AMAT) to generate earnings per share of $3.22 in 2017. This works out to an increase of 84.00% compared to last year’s earnings. For comparison’s sake, analysts expect the S&P 500 to grow earnings by an average of 12% in 2017. The average investment rating for AMAT on a scale of 1 to 5 (1 being a strong sell and 5 being a strong buy) is a 4.57 or a Moderate Buy. Three months ago, analysts assigned AMAT a 4.56 rating, which implies that analysts have become more optimistic about the outlook for the stock over the next year. TAGS",
