      "text": "Hershey Trust Company Decreased Hershey Company Com Stk Usd1 (NYSE:HSY) Stake By $490.50 Million \nOctober 24, 2017 - By Marguerite Chambers \nInvestors sentiment decreased to 0.98 in Q2 2017. Its down 0.25, from 1.23 in 2017Q1. It dropped, as 45 investors sold HSY shares while 217 reduced holdings. 64 funds opened positions while 194 raised stakes. 107.85 million shares or 0.45% more from 107.37 million shares in 2017Q1 were reported. Vanguard Grp invested 0.05% of its portfolio in Hershey Co (NYSE:HSY). First Personal Financial Services owns 1,305 shares. Regent Invest Mgmt Ltd Liability Company accumulated 2,020 shares. Blackrock reported 10.66M shares stake. Legal & General Grp Public Limited Company has 0.07% invested in Hershey Co (NYSE:HSY). Schwab Charles Investment Mgmt owns 463,696 shares for 0.05% of their portfolio. Kentucky Retirement Insur Tru Fund invested in 3,834 shares or 0.07% of the stock. Webster Bancorp N A reported 100 shares. Fmr Ltd Liability owns 0.02% invested in Hershey Co (NYSE:HSY) for 1.79 million shares. Cypress Capital Management Ltd Co (Wy) reported 115 shares stake. Rhumbline Advisers reported 312,205 shares. Voloridge Invest Mngmt Ltd Liability Com has 0.11% invested in Hershey Co (NYSE:HSY) for 40,086 shares. Bahl And Gaynor has invested 0.02% in Hershey Co (NYSE:HSY). Boston Private Wealth Ltd Liability Com holds 0.08% of its portfolio in Hershey Co (NYSE:HSY) for 18,652 shares. Bright Rock Cap Limited Liability Com stated it has 0.69% in Hershey Co (NYSE:HSY). \nSince May 1, 2017, it had 0 buys, and 11 sales for $12.09 million activity. Shares for $1.67M were sold by Wege D Michael. 37,875 shares valued at $4.31 million were sold by O’Day Terence L on Friday, June 9. Another trade for 22,065 shares valued at $2.54M was made by WALLING KEVIN R on Thursday, June 1. The insider Idrovo Javier H sold $577,390. The insider Buck Michele sold $270,756. 7,000 shares valued at $810,859 were sold by PALMER ANTHONY J. on Wednesday, May 31. \nHershey Trust Company decreased its stake in Hershey Company Com Stk Usd1 (NYSE:HSY) by 35.28% based on its latest 2017Q3 regulatory filing with the SEC. Hershey Trust Company sold 4.50 million shares as the company’s stock rose 4.41% with the market. The institutional investor held 8.25 million shares of the specialty foods company at the end of 2017Q3, valued at $901.04M, down from 12.75M at the end of the previous reported quarter. Hershey Trust Company who had been investing in Hershey Company Com Stk Usd1 for a number of months, seems to be less bullish one the $23.28 billion market cap company. The stock rose 0.43% or $0.47 reaching $109.59. About 158,542 shares traded. Hershey Co (NYSE:HSY) has risen 23.54% since October 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 6.84% the S&P500. Hershey Co (NYSE:HSY) Ratings Coverage \nAmong 18 analysts covering The Hershey Company ( NYSE:HSY ), 4 have Buy rating, 3 Sell and 11 Hold. Therefore 22% are positive. The Hershey Company has $11800 highest and $82 lowest target. $100.42’s average target is -8.37% below currents $109.59 stock price. The Hershey Company had 48 analyst reports since August 5, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The firm has “Hold” rating by Societe Generale given on Tuesday, February 28. The firm has “Hold” rating by Susquehanna given on Wednesday, July 26. The company was upgraded on Thursday, October 27 by Citigroup. The rating was downgraded by Bank of America on Wednesday, April 20 to “Underperform”. The company was maintained on Monday, February 6 by RBC Capital Markets. The stock of Hershey Co (NYSE:HSY) earned “Neutral” rating by JP Morgan on Tuesday, September 6. The firm has “Hold” rating given on Friday, June 23 by Stifel Nicolaus. The firm has “Hold” rating by Stifel Nicolaus given on Monday, October 31. The rating was maintained by Stifel Nicolaus with “Hold” on Thursday, August 31. The rating was upgraded by Tigress Financial on Wednesday, March 9 to “Buy”. \nThe Hershey Company is a producer of chocolate in North America. The company has market cap of $23.28 billion. The Company’s principal product offerings include chocolate and non-chocolate confectionery products; gum and mint refreshment products; pantry items, such as baking ingredients and beverages, and snack items, such as spreads, meat snacks, bars and snack bites and mixes. It has a 34.97 P/E ratio. The Company’s divisions include North America, and International and Other. \nMore recent Hershey Co (NYSE:HSY) news were published by: Streetinsider.com which released: “Form 4 HERSHEY CO For: Oct 16 Filed by: Wege D Michael” on October 18, 2017. Also Cnbc.com published the news titled: “Nestle US confectionery business draws attention from Hershey, others” on October 13, 2017. Marketwatch.com‘s news article titled: “Ferrero gobbles up Ferrara, eyes Nestle candy” with publication date: October 20, 2017 was also an interesting one. Receive News & Ratings Via Email - Enter your email address below to receive a concise daily summary of the latest news and analysts' ratings with our FREE daily email newsletter. Free Email Newsletter Enter your email address below to get the latest news and analysts' ratings for your stocks with our free daily email newsletter: Recent Posts",
