      "text": "Try to Download directly (2.55 MB) Play Press play then disable your screen reader. Use space bar to pause or play, and up and down arrows to control volume. Use left arrow to rewind and right arrow to fast forward. Image: Carbon emission reductions to \"flatline\" under new policy: backbencher \nBy Tom Iggulden on The World Today Share Download (2.55 MB) MP3 available 2.55 MB \nConservative Coalition MPs have been assured that reductions in carbon emissions will \"flatline\" for around a decade under the Government's new energy policy. \nThe chair of the Government's backbench energy committee, Craig Kelly, says no formal decision has been taken about the pace of carbon emission reductions.But he says he's been told, in closed-door briefings, to expect any reductions to happen slowly, if at all, until close to 2030. Duration: 5min 33sec Broadcast: Thu 19 Oct 2017, 12:03pm More Information \nCraig Kelly, MP, Chair of the backbench environment energy committee Credits",
