      "title": "Perth Stadium to be focal point for new marathon event",
      "country": "AU",
      "crawl_date": "2017-10-24T09:25:06Z",
      "url": "http://www.canberratimes.com.au/wa-news/perth-stadium-to-be-focal-point-for-new-marathon-event-20171024-gz705k.html",
      "host": "canberratimes.com.au",
      "text": "A new world-class marathon proposed by Athletics WA is set to boost tourism numbers in Perth.\nThe event is expected to be held in June 2019 to fit in with other major marathons in Australia.\nAthletics WA Chief Executive Officer Wayne Loxley told 6PR's Simon Beaumont they've been working with Tourism WA for the last two and a half years putting the event together, and the government had seen the benefits.\n\"They've given it the tick of approval,\" he said.\n\"We just need to find a bit of financial support with a sponsor to come on board and we're ready to go 2019.\"\nMr Loxley believes a marathon that puts Perth on the international map would be of interest to potential investors.\nAdvertisement \"Marathons have a unique way of selling their own worth,\" he said\n\"A West Australian company behind an event like this will give them good promotion and exposure, and be a great link for the community.\"\nThe 42-kilometre flat-fast course will start and finish at the new Perth stadium and will entail a series of festival events in the week leading up for primary school children.\n\"It's going to be the first community event that the stadium will have and of course that's also attractive to the government to bring people into the state,\" Mr Loxley said.\nAthletics WA has been in contact with British distance runner Mo Farah's management who said he is keen to get involved.\n\"Having these athletes involved brings every bit of attraction to the event,\" Mr Loxley said.\n\"Here in Perth, we're isolated - we need a world class event like this which brings people from all over the world to Perth and see how beautiful a place we live in.\n\"We've already had conversations with a major international TV company that would look at televising it for us and we think there's great interest in carrying the event for us,\" he said.\nMr Loxley is optimistic the marathon will be a success.\n\"We'd like to think we can get 5000 in the first year and I'm very confident it will grow from there.\"",
