      "host": "abetz.com.au",
      "text": "Another Department breaks ranks to breach APS Guidelines Written on 24 October 2017 . \nIn Senate Estimates today, it’s been revealed that the Department of Agriculture and Water Resources is implementing new union access rules in defiance of the APS Bargaining Policy. \nThe Department of Agriculture and Water Resources’ new Consultation and Representation Protocol , which can only be varied with the agreement of the CPSU, will allow CPSU material to be spammed to all employees, and have new workers subjected to a 45 minute union presentation encouraging new staff to join the union. \nThis follows the Department of Prime Minister and Cabinet implementing similar policies without the approval of the Prime Minister, the Public Service Minister nor the APS Commissioner. \n“Why on earth these departments feel it’s appropriate to dramatically expand union workplace access in defiance of the APS Bargaining Policy and without so much as a conversation with the Government is beyond me,” Senator Abetz said. \n“These draconian policies are clearly designed to try and increase CPSU membership at a time when union membership is on the decline and flies in the face of the principle of freedom of association.” \n“I look forward to the Department providing full responses to my questions and hope the Department will work to ditch this unnecessary impost on workers,” Senator Abetz concluded. About Eric \nEric Abetz has been a Liberal Senator for Tasmania since 1994 and has served in a range of Leadership, Ministerial and Shadow Ministerial roles.",
