      "title": "Canberra trainer Joe Ible's Maryore set to join Single Gaze on Melbourne Cup day",
      "country": "AU",
      "crawl_date": "2017-10-24T06:47:11Z",
      "url": "http://www.smh.com.au/sport/horseracing/canberra-trainer-joe-ibles-maryore-set-to-join-single-gaze-on-melbourne-cup-day-20171024-gz71gv.html",
      "host": "smh.com.au",
      "text": "Canberra trainer Joe Ible's Maryore set to join Single Gaze on Melbourne Cup day Chris Dutton twitter TWEET More \nEmerging trainer Joe Ible is hoping for a Canberra double on Melbourne Cup day as he sets Maryore for the biggest race of his young career. \nIble is set to enter Maryore in the group 3 Maybe Mahal Stakes (1400m) for mares at Flemington on Melbourne Cup day. SHARE Canberra horse Maryore is set to run on Melbourne Cup day. Photo: bradleyphotos.com.au \nIt will strengthen the capital's contingent at the marquee event of the spring carnival, with the 2017 provincial championship winner likely to join Nick Olive-trained Single Gaze on Australia's biggest horse racing stage. \nSingle Gaze will end Canberra's 12-year drought without a horse in the Melbourne Cup when she runs in the race that stops a nation on November 7. Related Articles \nIble and Maryore will also be there and the 27-year-old trainer says he's already starting to feel the nerves building a year after shifting his base to Canberra. \n\"You always dream of racing on these sorts of days,\" Ible said. Advertisement \n\"It's hard to say what her chances are without seeing the field yet, but she's getting towards that grade now. You will now receive updates from Sport Newsletter Sport Newsletter \nGet the latest news and updates emailed straight to your inbox. By submitting your email you are agreeing to Fairfax Media's terms and conditions and privacy policy . \n\"You dream of this sort of thing in your whole career so to be doing it now is exciting. The nerves are already there to be honest. But it's going to be a great day.\" \nMaryore was part of Philip Courtney's stable until recently relocating to join Ible's growing group of horses. \nIble has been training for the past five years after starting in Moruya and moving to Canberra 18 months ago. He has 16 horses in work and is hoping that number swells next year. \nMaryore could be the trigger for that with the six-year-old chasing her seventh win and her first since joining Ible. \nIble will take Maryore to Sydney next week for a trial and to work with jockey Tim Clark, who will jump on board on Melbourne Cup day. \n\"I wanted to grow the business and quality of horses. I'd like to get to 25 horses in the next 12 months and a winner on Melbourne Cup day would definitely help,\" Ible said. \n\"It has always been my attention to give [Maryore] just one or two races in the spring before setting her for an autumn campaign. She looks tremendous and has come back stronger.\" \nSingle Gaze finished second in the Caulfield Cup last weekend and will become the first Canberra horse since 2005 to race in the Melbourne Cup. \n\"It's an exciting time. Every stable out at Canberra jumps on board for these big races ... it just adds excitement to everything being done,\" Ible said.",
