      "title": "Confirmed: AFL heading back to China in 2018",
      "country": "AU",
      "crawl_date": "2017-10-24T02:34:46Z",
      "url": "https://www.foxsports.com.au/afl/afl-fixture-2018-china-game-port-adelaide-gold-coast-to-play-in-shanghai-in-round-9/news-story/23d73c8c37b0b51d256260cf5cc29b45",
      "host": "foxsports.com.au",
      "text": "Port Adelaide and Gold Coast will play in China for a second straight season. (AAP Image/Tracey Nearmy) Source: AAP THE AFL will play for premiership points in China for a second time in 2018. \nPort Adelaide’s ambitious play to the Asian nation will continue when it once again faces the Gold Coast Suns in Shanghai. \nThe ground has been christened as Adelaide Arena at Jiangwan Stadium, with the match to be played in Round 9 on the afternoon of Saturday May 19. \nThis season, the Power thumped the Suns by 72 points in front of 10,118 fans in Shanghai. The Power want to increase ticketing for 2018’s match to 13,000. \nBoth teams were given an early bye after the fixture to compensate for the long-distance travel. \nGold Coast has been forced to relocate several of its home games due to the 2018 Commonwealth Games being held in the city. \nThe Suns will not be able to play at Metricon Stadium until early June, but will play seven home games there after their return. \nGold Coast will face North Melbourne at Cairns’ Cazalys Stadium in Round 1. \nAFL 2018 FIXTURE — WHAT WE KNOW SO FAR \n* Port Adelaide v Gold Coast at Adelaide Arena at Jiangwan Stadium in Shanghai (Round 9, Saturday afternoon) \n* Gold Coast v North Melbourne at Cazalys Stadium (Round 1, Saturday night) \n* Round 1 will begin Thursday 22 March \n* Full AFL 2018 fixture to be released Tuesday 31 October View All Comments The latest sports news, in your inbox daily. Email",
