      "host": "theguardian.com",
      "text": "The Australian federal police have conducted raids on the Victorian and national headquarters of the Australian Workers Union.\nOfficers arrived at the Sydney and Melbourne offices of the union on Tuesday afternoon and an AFP spokeswoman confirmed officers had executed search warrants at both locations.\nIt is understood the searches relate to an investigation being conducted by the Registered Organisations Commission into whether donations made to the activist group GetUp by the AWU in 2005 were authorised under the union’s rules.\nLast month the employment minister, Michaelia Cash, referred GetUp funding to the Registered Organisations Commission after reports by News Corp that the AWU had donated large sums of money to GetUp in 2005 when Bill Shorten was the union’s secretary.\nThe Registered Organisations Commission, a new watchdog for unions and employer groups, was set up in response to the Heydon royal commission into union governance and corruption.\nTopics Australian trade unions Australian federal police Australian police and policing Michaelia Cash Coalition Australian politics",
